### ============================================
### Python 3
### ============================================

$   pacman -S python

Instal pip to get pypi libraries.

$   pacman -S python-pip

Install virtualenv to be able to create project specific environments.

$   pacman -S python-virtualenv

### ============================================
### Create Virtual Environment
### ============================================

1. Create a virtual environment.

$   virtualenv --python=/usr/bin/python3.3 virtual-environment --verbose

2. Test-run the virtual environment.

$   ./virtual-environmen/bin/pip-3.3 freeze


### ============================================
### Python 2
### ============================================

$   pacman -S python2

Instal pip to get pypi libraries.

$   pacman -S python2-pip

Install virtualenv to be able to create project specific environments.

$   pacman -S python2-virtualenv


### ============================================
### pydoc
### ============================================

Run the pydoc module that is included in the python distribution.

$   python /path/to/pydoc.py -p 1234

Where 1234 is the port you want the server to run at.
Then visit http://localhost:1234/ and browse the documentation.


### ============================================
### The Python REPL (the command-line interpreter / Read-Eval-Print-Loop)
### ============================================

To see a list of all available libs.

$   help("modules")

To see functions within a module.

$   help("posix")


